4. MoE Graph Construction
Why Mixture-of-Experts?
Financial documents contain multiple types of relationships that require specialized extraction techniques. A single monolithic approach cannot capture the rich semantics of cross-references, causal chains, temporal sequences, and entity mentions. Our MoE approach allows each expert to focus on its specific domain while contributing to a unified knowledge graph.
Expert Descriptions
CrossReferenceHunter
Discovers cross-references between documents using phrase matching ('See Note X', 'refer to') and embedding similarity
●	Edge Types: REFERS_TO
CausalChainBuilder
Identifies cause-effect relationships using causal language patterns (due to, resulted in, led to) and optional LLM extraction
●	Edge Types: CAUSED_BY, LEADS_TO
TemporalLinker
Links same financial items across time periods using XBRL tag matching, note numbers, section names, and embedding similarity
●	Edge Types: TEMPORAL_NEXT
TableTextConnector
Connects FINANCIAL_LINE nodes with explanatory TEXT_SECTION/NOTE nodes using embedding similarity and structural proximity
●	Edge Types: EXPLAINS_LINE_ITEM, DISCUSSES
SemanticBridge
Creates semantic similarity edges within and across filings, and adds BRIDGE edges to ensure graph connectivity
●	Edge Types: SEMANTICALLY_SIMILAR, BRIDGE
EntityExtractor
Extracts named entities (companies, products, executives) using LLM and links them across the graph [Optional, requires LLM]
●	Edge Types: MENTIONS_ENTITY, ENTITY_RELATED_TO
Expert Execution Order (from experts/__init__.py)
Experts are executed SERIALLY (one after another) in dict insertion order (Python 3.7+). This ensures edges created by earlier experts are available for later experts:
●	1. CrossReferenceHunter - REFERS_TO
●	2. CausalChainBuilder - CAUSED_BY, LEADS_TO
●	3. TemporalLinker - TEMPORAL_NEXT
●	4. TableTextConnector - EXPLAINS_LINE_ITEM, DISCUSSES
●	5. SemanticBridge - SEMANTICALLY_SIMILAR, BRIDGE
●	6. EntityExtractor - MENTIONS_ENTITY, ENTITY_RELATED_TO
Serial execution rationale:
●	CrossReferenceHunter runs first to establish document-level connections
●	CausalChainBuilder identifies cause-effect before temporal links
●	TemporalLinker can use cross-references to find same items across periods
●	TableTextConnector bridges financial ↔ narrative domains
●	SemanticBridge runs LAST to ensure graph connectivity after all structural edges exist
●	EntityExtractor is optional (requires LLM) and creates entity nodes
