5. Dual Operator Architecture
Quantum Mechanics Analogy
In quantum mechanics, non-commuting operators yield different results depending on the order of application. Similarly, our dual operators represent complementary perspectives on the knowledge graph - one grounded in quantitative structure, the other in qualitative narrative. The commutator measures how much these perspectives disagree, guiding the system's confidence and exploration strategy.
Operator A: Structure-First (Numbers → Narrative)
Philosophy: Start from authoritative financial data and traverse toward explanatory context.
●	Seed Node Types: FINANCIAL_LINE
●	Starting Point: Direct XBRL tag matching for revenue/expense/profit queries
●	Minimum Financial Nodes in Evidence: 3
Operator A Edge Selection (from operators.py)
Edge selection is dynamic based on explore_weight (w):
●	Base edges (always): EXPLAINS_LINE_ITEM, DISCUSSES, TEMPORAL_NEXT, REFERS_TO
●	Extended edges (w > 0.4): + CAUSED_BY
●	Extended edges (w > 0.6): + MENTIONS_ENTITY
●	Note: SEMANTICALLY_SIMILAR is intentionally EXCLUDED to prevent drift
Operator B: Narrative-First (Narrative → Numbers)
Philosophy: Start from contextual narrative and traverse toward supporting financial data.
●	Seed Node Types: TEXT_SECTION, NOTE
●	Starting Point: Embedding similarity search over TEXT_SECTION and NOTE nodes
●	Minimum Financial Nodes in Evidence: 2
Operator B Edge Selection (from operators.py)
Edge selection is dynamic based on explore_weight (w):
●	Base edges (always): EXPLAINS_LINE_ITEM, DISCUSSES, CAUSED_BY, MENTIONS_ENTITY
●	Extended edges (w < 0.5): + TEMPORAL_NEXT
●	Extended edges (w > 0.6 AND hop == 1): + SEMANTICALLY_SIMILAR
Note: SEMANTICALLY_SIMILAR is only allowed on hop 1 during exploration, and the scoring system applies heavy drift penalties regardless.
Convergence Pressure Mechanism
When evidence divergence (Δ_E) exceeds 0.8, the system applies convergence pressure by sharing top evidence nodes between operators. This encourages operators to explore overlapping regions of the graph.
 
6. The Commutator
Commutator Formula
Δ(q, h) = w_E · Δ_E + w_V · Δ_V + w_A · Δ_A + w_C · Δ_C
Where Δ measures total divergence at query q and hop h
Component Weights
Component	Weight	Description
Δ_E (Evidence)	0.30	Jaccard distance between retrieved node sets
Δ_V (Structural)	0.20	Jaccard distance on (section, type, period) tuples
Δ_A (Answer)	0.30	Cosine distance between answer embeddings
Δ_C (Confidence)	0.20	Difference in path confidence statistics
Component Formulas
Evidence Divergence (Δ_E)
Δ_E = 1 - |E_A ∩ E_B| / |E_A ∪ E_B|
Measures overlap between evidence sets using Jaccard distance. Range: [0, 1] where 0 = identical sets, 1 = completely disjoint.
Structural Divergence (Δ_V)
Δ_V = 1 - |V_A ∩ V_B| / |V_A ∪ V_B| where V = {(section, type, period)}
Measures structural coverage differences. High Δ_V indicates operators are looking at different parts of the document structure.
Answer Divergence (Δ_A)
Δ_A = 1 - cos(φ(a_A), φ(a_B)) where φ = FinBERT embedding
Measures semantic difference between generated answers. Critical for determining if operators agree on the conclusion.
Confidence Divergence (Δ_C)
Δ_C = 0.6 · |μ_A - μ_B| + 0.4 · |σ_A - σ_B| / max(σ_A, σ_B, ε)
Captures disagreement in confidence levels. High Δ_C indicates one operator is certain while the other is uncertain.
Interpretation Guide
Δ Range	Interpretation	Recommended Action
< 0.25	Strong convergence - operators agree	EXPLOIT: Trust the answer
0.25 - 0.6	Partial convergence	ADAPTIVE: Merge with caveats
> 0.6	High divergence - significant disagreement	EXPLORE: Present multiple perspectives
 
7. Mode Selection System
The Three Modes
EXPLOIT Mode
Triggered when operators strongly agree. System provides a single, confident answer.
●	Condition: Δ < 0.25 OR strong answer agreement (Δ_A < 0.15)
●	Confidence Range: 0.70 - 0.95
●	Output: Direct answer from most reliable operator
ADAPTIVE Mode
Triggered when operators partially agree. System merges perspectives with appropriate caveats.
●	Condition: 0.25 ≤ Δ ≤ 0.6
●	Confidence Range: 0.50 - 0.75
●	Output: Merged answer with reliability weighting
EXPLORE Mode
Triggered when operators significantly disagree. System presents multiple perspectives.
●	Condition: Δ > 0.6 OR diverging trajectory OR opinion query
●	Confidence Range: 0.30 - 0.55
●	Output: Dual hypothesis with explicit uncertainty
